        "timestamp": "2018-11-12 11:16:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(6 comments)\n\nHi Ram,\n\nI tried what you suggested. I removed the dependency plugin and ant plugin eclipse profiles from the submodule POMs and amended the eclipse profile in the main POM.\n\nWhen I did that, I got packaging errors on the submodules in Eclipse, even when I deleted the modules out of eclipse, cleared down the eclipse settings by deleting the .classpath/.project/.settings files and re-imporing.\n\nHowever, when I added back the eclipse profile in only one submodule, the errors disappeared on them all!!!!!\n\nTherefore, as becoming an expert on debugging Eclipse/Maven interaction is not all that high on my todo list [;-)], i just put the profiles back into all the submodules.\n\nI did fix the versions on the Eclipse profiles to be consistent though.\n\nStill, we should document this somewhere so that we know we have to put in Eclipse profiles for the dependency plugin in the actual submodule POMs.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
